en_100444_0	According to activists, the year 2014 was the deadliest year yet in Syria's four-year conflict, with over 76,000 killed.
en_100444_1	The UK-based Syrian Observatory for Human Rights said 17,790 of the dead were civilians, including 3,501 children.
en_100444_2	Meanwhile more than 15,000 died in conflicts in Iraq in 2014, making it that country's worst year since 2007.
en_100444_3	Much of the violence comes as a result of advances by Islamic State and other militant groups in the two countries.
en_100444_4	US-led air strikes against IS militants, fighting between government troops and rebels in Syria, and sectarian violence in Iraq have also accounted for large numbers of deaths.
